	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=66620"><span id=" ">Slein</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">235 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Default [1.85]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Multiquested items ARE no drop.&nbsp;&nbsp;There would be no point in MQ if they were dropable.  The way MQ works is the person with the item they are MQing (for someone else) gives the item to the quest NPC, then the person who is intended to recieve the item gives the NPC the rest of the components and gets the item.  (Whoever turns in the last piece gets the final reward...).  Not all nodrop quest items can be MQed tho, seeing as the other components are probably difficult to come buy, do your research before giving it a shot...</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Ok, I'll shut up now.<br/><br/>Slein Jinn<br/>Dread Lord on everyone's least favorite server, E'ci<br/><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=325772" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=325772</a></td></tr>
